				<article class="content">
					<section class="biome-intro">
						<h2>Biome Overview</h2>
						<p>The Forest Cluster is a sprawling wilderness of ancient trees, winding rivers, and hidden cave systems. From the sun-drenched Canopy Heights to the murky depths of Sunken Caverns, this biome hosts a diverse ecosystem of creatures adapted to vertical terrain and low-light environments.</p>

						<div class="zones-section">
							<h3>Zones</h3>
							<div class="zone-tags">
								<span class="zone-tag">🌊 River Basin</span>
								<span class="zone-tag">🌿 Verdant Hollow</span>
								<span class="zone-tag">🌳 Canopy Heights</span>
								<span class="zone-tag">🕳️ Sunken Caverns</span>
								<span class="zone-tag">🌲 Forest Valley</span>
							</div>
						</div>
