						<!-- THORNBACK BOAR -->
						<div class="creature-card">
							<div class="creature-header">
								<div class="creature-title">
									<h3>Thornback Boar</h3>
									<span class="creature-tagline">Bristled Menace</span>
								</div>
								<div class="creature-meta">
									<span class="tier-badge tier-0">Tier 0</span>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-info-bar">
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Classification:</strong> Minor Beast
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Element:</strong> None
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Zones:</strong> River Basin, Verdant Hollow
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Skittish charger, lashes out when cornered
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>📖 Lore</h4>
								<p>Thornback Boars are lean, aggressive wild boars covered in hardened, needle-like bristles. Usually scavengers, they turn hostile when startled or when hunters get too close to their feeding grounds. Despite being small, their reckless charges can disrupt formation and push hunters into riverbeds, mud pits, or larger threats lurking nearby.</p>
								<p>They are considered a nuisance, not a hunt — but an angry Thornback can easily create chaos in the wrong terrain.</p>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>📊 Stats & Attributes</h4>
								<div class="stats-grid">
									<div class="stat-block">
										<div class="stat-row"><span>STR</span><strong>4 (+2)</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>DEX</span><strong>3 (+1)</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>CON</span><strong>3 (+1)</strong></div>
									</div>
									<div class="stat-block">
										<div class="stat-row"><span>INT</span><strong>2 (+1)</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>INS</span><strong>4 (+2)</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>CHA</span><strong>2 (+1)</strong></div>
									</div>
									<div class="stat-block combat-stats">
										<div class="stat-row"><span>AR</span><strong>8</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>HP</span><strong>22</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>Stamina</span><strong>13</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>Movement</span><strong>40 ft burst / 25 ft normal</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>Attacks/Turn</span><strong>1</strong></div>
									</div>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>🗡️ Attacks & Abilities</h4>
								<div class="ability-list">
									<div class="ability">
										<div class="ability-header">
											<strong>Gore Jab</strong>
											<span class="ability-cost">1 Stamina • Melee (STR)</span>
										</div>
										<p><strong>Attack:</strong> d20 + 4 | <strong>Damage:</strong> 1d6 + 2</p>
										<p>On a natural 18-20, the target must succeed a DEX Save (DC 10) or be knocked back 5 ft.</p>
									</div>

									<div class="ability">
										<div class="ability-header">
											<strong>Spine-Bristle Buck</strong>
											<span class="ability-cost">1 Stamina</span>
										</div>
										<p>When a hunter is adjacent at the start of the boar's turn, the Thornback thrashes its bristles.</p>
										<p><strong>Damage:</strong> 1d4 piercing</p>
										<p>Targets must pass a CON Save (DC 10) or suffer Bleed.</p>
									</div>
								</div>

								<div class="special-trait">
									<strong>🐗 Special Trait — Instinctive Charge</strong>
									<p>If the Thornback moves 20 ft in a straight line before attacking, its next Gore Jab deals +1d4 damage. If it hits, it immediately attempts to disengage 10 ft after the attack.</p>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>💀 Behavior</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Flees if reduced below 25% HP</li>
									<li>Charges the closest visible threat</li>
									<li>Startles easily — loud noises or sudden movement may trigger an accidental charge</li>
									<li>Often travels in pairs, especially near food sources</li>
								</ul>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>🎒 Loot Table</h4>
