										<div class="stat-row"><span>Movement</span><strong>20 ft ground / 40 ft climb / 60 ft glide</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>Attacks/Turn</span><strong>1</strong></div>
									</div>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>🗡️ Attacks & Abilities</h4>
								<div class="ability-list">
									<div class="ability">
										<div class="ability-header">
											<strong>Vinebite Snap</strong>
											<span class="ability-cost">1 Stamina • Melee (DEX)</span>
										</div>
										<p><strong>Attack:</strong> d20 + 4 | <strong>Damage:</strong> 1d6 + 3</p>
									</div>

									<div class="ability">
										<div class="ability-header">
											<strong>Glide Kick</strong>
											<span class="ability-cost">1 Stamina</span>
										</div>
										<p>Must descend from at least 10 ft elevation.</p>
										<p><strong>Damage:</strong> 1d4 + 3</p>
										<p>Target must succeed a DEX Save (DC 10) or be knocked off balance: –5 ft movement next turn.</p>
									</div>
								</div>

								<div class="special-trait">
									<strong>🌿 Special Trait — Skyvine Glide</strong>
									<p>The drake can glide up to 60 ft in a straight line as a free movement once per turn if it begins its turn at a higher elevation. It cannot glide if restrained, grounded, or wings damaged.</p>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>🧗 Behavior</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Avoids direct combat; flees if reduced below 50% HP</li>
									<li>Constantly moves between branches</li>
									<li>Will attempt to steal before it attacks</li>
									<li>Often appears in groups of 2–4, especially near fruit-heavy trees</li>
									<li>May bait hunters into dangerous positions (cliff edges, unstable branches)</li>
								</ul>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>💰 Loot Table</h4>
								<table class="loot-table">
									<thead>
										<tr>
											<th>Drop</th>
