						<!-- DUSKHORN VIPER -->
						<div class="creature-card">
							<div class="creature-header">
								<div class="creature-title">
									<h3>Duskhorn Viper</h3>
									<span class="creature-tagline">Cavern Ambusher</span>
								</div>
								<div class="creature-meta">
									<span class="tier-badge tier-0">Tier 0</span>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-info-bar">
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Classification:</strong> Serpent Beast
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Element:</strong> None
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Zones:</strong> Sunken Caverns, Forest Valley
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Camouflaged ambusher, skittish but venomous
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>📖 Lore</h4>
								<p>Duskhorn Vipers are slender, grey-green snakes that hide among cavern moss, roots, and damp forest debris. Their scales reflect just enough ambient light to blend into walls and undergrowth.</p>
								<p>They rarely attack deliberately — most bites come from accidental steps, misjudged reaches, or startled proximity. Their venom is weak but disruptive, designed to deter rather than kill.</p>
								<p>Hunters consider them a nuisance hazard in dark environments, especially when multiple vipers slither into the same choke-point.</p>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>📊 Stats & Attributes</h4>
								<div class="stats-grid">
									<div class="stat-block">
										<div class="stat-row"><span>STR</span><strong>1 (+0)</strong></div>
