						<!-- PALAX -->
						<div class="creature-card">
							<div class="creature-header">
								<div class="creature-title">
									<h3>Palax</h3>
									<span class="creature-tagline">Child of the Burrow</span>
								</div>
								<div class="creature-meta">
									<img class="creature-portrait" src="/monsters/Meridia/Forest Cluster/Palax.png" alt="Palax" />
									<span class="tier-badge tier-1">Tier 1</span>
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-info-bar">
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Classification:</strong> Rodent Beast
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Element:</strong> None
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Zones:</strong> Verdant Hollow, The Burrows (hidden)
								</div>
								<div class="info-item">
									<strong>Behavior:</strong> Territorial subterranean ambusher
								</div>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>📖 Lore</h4>
								<p>Palax are massive, blind mole-rats adapted to life entirely underground. Their bodies are compact and muscular, with reinforced skulls and claws optimized for burrowing. They navigate through seismic sensitivity—feeling vibrations through the soil rather than seeing or hearing. Though not naturally aggressive, they respond violently to threats near their tunnels, erupting from below in explosive bursts of dirt and debris.</p>
								<p>Many believe Palax to be juveniles of a deeper species that dwells far beneath the forest.</p>
							</div>

							<div class="creature-section">
								<h4>📊 Stats & Attributes</h4>
								<div class="stats-grid">
									<div class="stat-block">
										<div class="stat-row"><span>STR</span><strong>7 (+3)</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>DEX</span><strong>6 (+3)</strong></div>
										<div class="stat-row"><span>CON</span><strong>6 (+3)</strong></div>
									</div>
